race.comment: STORM LEOPARD (5) looks a promising type by last year's Victoria Derby-winning sire Ghaiyyath who turned in a good performance last start back in trip off a freshen following a good maiden win. He'll have taken great benefit from that, will relish stepping back up in trip and draws to get a good run. SUBTLE POWER (11) doesn't boast the best winning strike rate but ran a nice race last time out, finishing fourth and beaten only 2 lengths over 1755m at Geelong after being prominent at the turn. Doesn't know how to run poorly. SAKAKIBARA (7) was a massive drifter - $19 out to $41 - on debut but was still able to win, so with improvement from that you'd think she'll be even better. DANCE LADY (13) next elect.
